so, I had smaller collections of coins, bells, stones, shells, marbles, dice, pins, buttons (both kinds) all which I still have some of and collector cards about cryptids which I don't. 

I really liked sharing stuff that's given me joy, let me know any fun collections u had!

Let's see, clock gears! Not plastic of aesthetic replicas, real brass movements still together, I love cams and gears and suck as much as keys! Aesthetic/fidget bliss. 

I'm running out of steam on this lol

Next was what I called 'car lables' silver painted plastic make/model words on cars. I got as many as I could with a mechanic parent who'd visit a wrecking yard and take them home for free - 100s. thought about doing stop motion with individual letters, made 2 gifs lol

tiny luggage keys into a strip of complex chainmail with metal/garnet beads occasionally integrated that looked so fucking cool.) I kept most in a cigar box but had giant skeleton key replicas and wall hangings. I. Loved. Keys.

so. I ran with that and hoarded keys with no practical use- all that I could find. I eventually outgrew the belief but not the aesthetic and had hundreds of many varieties ( I'd melt plastic off ignition keys which left 2/3 small rings diecut on the top and wove these with

Now the object list is going to get stranger. CW: religious... strangeness

I collected keys since 6/7 yrs old due to... odd religious indoctrination not meshing with literal interpretation. I was told more keys = more authority = from god = more spiritual protection

Hotwheels I liked because I had a metal one with worn away paint from my dad that he had 60 years ago as a kid. I collected and loved playing with them, then just having them around. Both of the bulk of these collections got rehomed to children. :3

I think the most bland ones to get out of the way are hotwheels and books: i had 100s. Waaaay more hundreds of books and I miss them. I think I had possibly over a thousand at its largest but have gradually pared down to just over a dozen moving frequently over the years.

I was reminiscing about some cool collections I had as a kid/ young adult and I enjoy talking about them even though I don't have them anymore, so if u want to read about my funky little things, read below!
